dcterms:description: Spatial action maps are used to select the next action for a robot equipped with a blower to move scattered objects into a target receptacle, allowing for efficient learning of vision-based policies that combine high-level planning and low-level control.

dcterms:description: PyBullet is a physics simulation module used for simulating blowing by shooting small invisible spherical 'wind' particles out of the blower, allowing for realistic interaction with objects in the environment.
dcterms:title: PyBullet

dcterms:description: Dynamic Movement Primitives (DMPs) are used to produce stable units of control that can be sequenced or blended together for downstream tasks, facilitating the learning of complex motor behaviors.
dcterms:title: Dynamic Movement Primitives (DMPs)

dcterms:description: Hierarchical Reinforcement Learning (HRL) is utilized to issue commands from a high-level policy to a low-level policy, allowing for structured learning and execution of tasks.
dcterms:title: Hierarchical Reinforcement Learning

dcterms:description: Reinforcement Learning with Sequences of Motion Primitives allows for robust manipulation by combining learned sequences of actions to achieve complex tasks.
